# Axis 17 — no prefix / main replay

Resuming a saved continuation invokes the resume entry directly at the capture point —
the computation before the capture (the prefix) is never re-executed. Verified by a
prefix with an observable side effect: a counter that must fire exactly once, at
capture, not again on each `run`. The saved value is run twice, yet the counter stays 1.

```scalascript
case class SavedContinuation[A, R](k: A => R):
  def run(value: A): R = k(value)

def save[A, R](k: A => R): SavedContinuation[A, R] = SavedContinuation(k)

var prefixRuns = 0

multi effect Suspend:
  def point(): Int

val saved: SavedContinuation[Int, Int] = save(handle {
  prefixRuns = prefixRuns + 1
  val input = Suspend.point()
  input * 10
} {
  case Suspend.point(k) => k
})

println(saved.run(1))
println(saved.run(2))
println(prefixRuns)
```
